I JHM Graw, Sheriff of King County W.T. do hereby certify that I receive the annexed Execution out the 13th day of November, 1885 and by virtue and in persuance thereof, I on the 14th day of Novemeber 1885 duly lived, upon seized and I tool into my custody in King County, W.T. as the property of the defendant named in said writ the following described personal property to wit
2 Small Harses, 1-3 Spring Wagon and 1 set Doublee Harwess

That I advertised said property to be sold by me at the City Stablis in the City of Seattle, King County W.T. on the 30th day of November 1885 by posting written notices of said sale in threr off the most public places in said City.

That before the day fixed for said sale, to wit, on the 18th day of November 1885 one Mrs Leud Hutchinson calaimed to be the owun of said property, and having proved to my satisfaction the validity of her said claim, I by her order, deft said property in the
custody of H.F. Philliper & Co in said County, subject to the order of her the said Leud Hutchinson
I hereby further cutify that I am unable to fuid any property in my County on which to make the ammont of the said execution or any part thereof.
Solid at Seattle the 3rd day of December 1885
JHM Graw Sheriff By DRM Kuilay Dep.
Sheriffs Fees Levy $1.00 Copy Writ .80 Frauce .20 Posting Notices 1.50 Copies 2.40 Frace .20 Swearing Keeper .25 Return of Writ 1.00 7.30
UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
Territory of Wahington Third Judicial District } ss. No. 4704
To the Sheriff of King County, Greeting: WHEREAS, G. W. Hutchinson recovered judgment against W.H. Harris.

in the District Court for the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding terms at Seattle, on the 13th day of November A.D. 1885 for the sum of Costs of Suit Dollars with interest at the rate ofuntil paid, and cost of suit amounting to Seventeen $100 - ($17. 40 Dollars. THEREFORE, in the name of the United States of America, you are hereby commanded forthwith to levy upon, seize and take into execution, the personal property of the said W.H. Harris in your County, sufficient subjet to execution to satisfy said judgment, interest and increased interest, cost and increased cost, and make sale therof accordiing to law; and if sufficient personal proprerty cannot be found, then you are further commanded to make the amount of said judgment, interest and increased interest, cost and increased cost, out of his real property, not exempt by law, and make retun of this writ whithin sixty days from the date hereof.
Herein fail not and have you then and there this writ
WITNESS the Hon. Roger S. Greene, Chief Justice of the Supreme Court, and Judge of the Third Judcial District of Washington Territory, and the Seal of said Court, this 13th day of November A.D. 1885
JAMES SEAVEY, Clerk
By James P Ludlow Deputy Clerk
IN THE DISTRICT COURT, THIRD JUDICIAL DISTRICT
G.W. Hutchinson VS. W.H. Herris
EXECUTION
Judgment for $Burts Interest at per cent $ Increased Interest, $ Cost, $ 17.40 Clerk's Increased Cost, $ .70 Sheriff's Increased Cost, $
